text:
Sells Asian / Chinese Vegetarian food with vegan options ( do inform the staff if you do not want eggs )
Food contains no alliums.

Though the stall looks like a typical Chinese vegetarian stall, I think their vegetables curry is one of the best in Singapore, flavourful with just the right amount of spiciness and sweetness. Will definitely choose it again the next time I go.
Price is reasonable too with friendly service.

The vegetarian beehoon!! Amazing üòç love the curry vegetable, beehoon taste mildly seasoned with less salt and oil which is good.

The mock goose and Mock char siew is fresh with no weird bean taste.

All in all very value for money!

Will come back again!

New stall that replace Huay Jin Vegetarian. Much more variety as compare to Huay Jin. They have Laksa, Mee Rebus and normal Zar Char like hor fun, fried rice and so on....

Normal vegetarian food price. Example a normal plate of Vegetarian Mee Hoon cost around $4.

Same standard as of Huay Jin just that their curry veg can be cold at time.

If you are nearby and need a vegetarian food fix, can try ah.....
Open daily: 6am to 8pm,  Zhi char from 11am -8pm friendly cook, more varieties Mala pot port,fried oysters eggs, hor fun, sweet sour monkey head mushrooms rice, etc
Bought veg food from this stall. Is this a full-fledged veg stall? Because one of the dishes I ordered seem to contain meat items. Please clarify.
